5:
Are you really sure about this, Toria?
What would a sacred Mirean relic be
doing in a village like this?
9:
I am sure! Many of Mirea's sacred
relics were unfortunately taken out
of the country during periods of
internal trouble.
13:
It falls upon me to retrieve them all!
That is my great dutyâ€”alongside
the conquest of Palpebra, of course.
17:
You expect me to believe something
that valuable is just gonna be lying
around in a village in the boonies?
21:
There's no need for concern! I assure
you, our intelligence network is
seldom wrong.
23:
After my grandfather pawned the
relic off, it finally found its way to this
very village.
27:
Here's a thought, how about not
pawning off your country's sacred
relics?
30:
Mirea's sacred relicâ€”the Necklace of
Elmyra! I will reclaim it, no matter
the cost!
34:
All right then... I guess it can't hurt to
ask around the village.
40:
Well, that was... a lot faster than I
anticipated!
43: I can't believe it! How could this be...
46:
The necklace is no mere prize!
Especially not one to be fought over
in some primitive test of strength!
50:
What's that? You lot taken an
interest in our little tournament here?
52: For one reason or another, yeah.
55:
Is it okay for people not from this
village to participate?
58:
Eager to join in at the last minute,
eh? Be my guest!
61:
So, all you need to do is take down
your opponent like that? Seems
straightforward enough.
65:
Are you suggesting I, a princess of a
foreign nation, enter into this brawl?
70:
I mean, you're the best one for the
job.
75:
Yes. Your abilities are incredible,
Toria. I want to see them in action.
81:
Hmm. I suppose I have no choice,
then!
84:
Wait a minuteâ€”are you absolutely
sure? Someone as... small as you
could get hurt in a fight like this!
87:
Oh, is that so? I'll have to be extra
careful then. Hehe.
93:
Well then! Let's get started. Attack
me!
96:
If you're sure about this, I guess we
can have one bout.... I'll do my best
not to hurt youâ€”
99:
Okay, now the rest of you! All at the
same time, please!
103:
It's hard to overstate my
disappointment here... Is that really
the best you can do?!
106:
Holy smokes, I've never seen a girl as
strong as you in my life! You
definitely deserve this prize...
109:
Rejoice! I finally did it! I've finally
reclaimed one of the sacred relics of
Mirea!
120:
Wait... No, it couldn't be...
This...
125:
This isn't Elmyra's Necklace! It's a
fake!
129:
What is the meaning of this? Did you
really think you can deceive me with
a counterfeit?
132:
N-now that you mention it, I
remember my dad talking about
this a long time ago. He told me this
necklace was just a replacement!
134:
It turns out the real one got stolen
by a crow during a feast way back
when.
141:
And here I thought I'd finally found a
sacred relic...
145: T-Toria! Calm down, it'll be okay!
149:
Hold on. You said the culprit was a
crow, yes? I see a nest up in that
tree with something glittering inside
it... Could that be your relic?
153:
Glittering? Yes, yes, that could be
Elmyra's Necklace!
155: I can't believe it! What luck...
160:
It's woven pretty tightly into that
nest though. It'll be hard to extract it...
164:
So? Just take the nest apart.
Problem solved.
168:
But that would mean destroying it,
leaving a poor bird without a home!
How unconscionable!
172:
The heavens have chosen to test
my prowess as a stateswomanâ€”I
must prove myself and resolve this
diplomatically!
176:
Right... I figured we could just build
the bird a new nest to replace the
one we destroy.
183:
I honestly can't tell if you're making
fun of me or not, but whatever.
188:
In the meantime, let's speak to the
villagers. They might have materials
suitable for building a nest.
198:
There you go! Nice to make some
progress on your quest to get the
relics, right?
202:
Can we go home yet? I don't even
know why I came alongâ€”all I did
was watch a little girl beat up grown
men.
206:
Go home? What are you talking
about? We need to go searching for
the next of the sacred relics!
208:
There are approximately seven of
them in a village nearbyâ€”
212:
S-seven?! Wait a minute, just exactly
how many are there in total?!
215:
Not counting the necklace?
One hundred and twenty-seven.
220:
E-excuse me?! Why does a country
even need that many?!
225:
Because that's precisely how many
we have! Regardless, we don't have
time to restâ€”we must be off!
229:
This better not be for your own
personal collection or something...
